Folks,<div><br></div><div>I ran some basic tests with IPM profiler-like <a href="https://github.com/nerscadmin/IPM">https://github.com/nerscadmin/IPM</a> and found that when fortran calls an mpi subroutine, this is accounted twice.</div><div>IPM defines both MPI_* subroutines and their fortran mpi_*_ counterpart.</div><div>since the ompi fortran calls the MPI_* symbol (and not the PMPI_* one), and IPM does nothing to prevent double accounting, all subroutines are accounted twice</div><div><br></div><div>what is the rationale for calling MPI_* from fortran instead of PMPI_* ?</div><div><br></div><div>basically, I can see three options</div><div>1. we do nothing, this is an IPM problem, not an Open MPI one</div><div>2. we change ompi to call the PMPI_* symbols</div><div>3. we add a configure option to call PMPI_* symbols instead of the MPI_* ones</div><div><br></div><div>any thoughts ?</div><div><br></div><div>Cheers,</div><div><br></div><div>Gilles<br><br></div>

